			<div>
				<h5>Calendar &amp; Site Info</h5>
				<p>I try to post homework due dates and exam dates on the calendar side tab. I also like to setup our course page to allow students to email other students, the entire class, or even groups within the class. You can join one of these groups through the site info tab. The online groups allow you to communicate easily with study groups via your university email to ask questions, schedule study group sessions, and any other class related topics.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h5>Email &amp; Mailing List Archive</h5>
				<p>You have the ability to email the entire class. This needs to be used for class. There are plenty of other sites and apps for all of your other communications needs. All the emails that I send to the entire class will be kept and stored in the Mailing List Archive.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h5>Gradebook 2 &amp; Attendance</h5>
				<p>Grades and attendance will be recorded and posted online. I’m not perfect, and may make a mistake in entering a grade. Please let me know as soon as possible if this is the case. I will ask to see your graded assignment to double check, and then will correct my error. So keep all graded work that gets returned to you.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h5>Questions and Answers</h5>
				<p>This is where you can ask questions of me and of your fellow students. Most importantly, your questions and answers will be anonymous to everyone, including myself, unless you add your name or other identifying information to the post. You can also be notified via email whenever people respond to your question.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
